for those of you who say the movie isnt any good, then i doubt you watched the old versions of the 3 stooges. I found it pretty funny the entire movie.

Folks...This is based on slapstick comedy.  The Three Stooges started in the 1920s in Vaudeville acts and, well, at the time the blows had to be real (so Moe slapping Larry would be heard in the back of the theater).  This movie recreates that slapstick comedy with a modern twist.  The slaps, eyepokes, hammers to skull and even the lobster down Larry's pants with IMPLIED nutcracker are sound effects and "selling" the shot.  Moe slaps Larry. sound guy hits a button on the console, Larry sells the move and makes sound of pain.  Easy.  or Moe eyepokes Snooki and he hits in the upper part of the orbital bone, Snooki sells the move by yelling OW and putting her hand to her face.

It's a more physical comedy, people, and if you're too bent on being PC...don't bother watching this...go back to Bill and Ted.
